result.name: Crystal Jade - Central

reviews.text: Exellent food at affordable price. Stewed pork belly is melt-in-your-mouth tender and super tasty. Conch salad is refreshingly good. Will definitely come back for more.

Arrived during peak hour and had to wait outside which is fine. It’s one of my favourite restaurants in Hong Kong so I didn’t mind waiting. The staff were quite rude, then served the table next to us even though we were seated first. I wanted to order from the vegetarian menu and everything I wanted was sold out? Not sure how noodles can’t just be cooked without meat? 
The alternatives they suggested were gross and overall it wasn’t a nice experience. Oh and the aircon is freezing!
Broad menu, solid preparation, decent prices and prompt service. Can't go wrong.

Excellent food at a reasonable price. This is one of my favourite restaurant for family lunch. The xiaolungbao is one of the best in Hong Kong. Various types of noodles are also wonderful. I like the Shanghai Thick Noodle. Highly recommended!
I was expecting amazing food but maybe my expectation was too high. Dimsim was good but noodle we ordered was quite disappointing.

result.name: ifc mall

reviews.text: ifc is probably one of the best malls in Hong Kong. With the wide variety of food and the even wider variety of clothing, this makes the mall a comfortable and one of the best malls. The train station is also located near the mall for easier access and convenient travel. Would definitely recommend to tourists and travelers.

Huge open shopping mall with plenty of restaurants and great connections throughout Hong Kong be they ferry, train, buses or even the airport express. There are plenty of open areas, including the rooftop area which is reserved for restaurants and bars. The area has a luxury vibe at a corresponding price tag.
Probably one of my favorite malls in the world. You can find here basically anything, from Shake Shack, to cold-pressed juices, clothing stores, Apple, electronics and much more.

Hong Kong is full of places like this. Shopping mall stuffed with expensive brands, an Apple store and a cinema. There is a city super and if you want a decent coffee go to fuel. It also has a music shop with a pretty good selection of new vinyl. Best thing to do here? Buy some beers from city super or nearby marks and Spencers and head up to the Mall roof top garden and watch Kowloon as the sun goes down, or a storm is coming in. Pretty awesome.
Excellent mall, just above the Hong Kong train station. Has excellent options for shopping and food which includes all varieties. Overall excellent place.

result.name: 翡翠拉麵小籠包 - 中環

reviews.text: 小籠包👍
這間餐廳好污糟，用過嘅紙巾給客人用丶 小碗中有小蟲子， 侍應 一句抱歉話都沒有說！！！差評！🤮🤮🤮😠😠😠第—次給餐廳差評！
한국에도 있지만 확실히 매장마다의 차이가있습니다. 이름은 정확히 기억못하지만 사이드로 주문한 오이 가지요리는 찾는사람이 적지만 실패하지않는 메뉴로 확실히 보장합니다 그외 메뉴들은 워낙 유명해서 생략합니다
服務水準差，侍應生明明有很多，都只在和同事互相談話，不理客人，明明餐點不錯，又不幫客人倒茶，要三吹四請至肯做！經常下錯單漏單！不建議食客到此一遊！

Die Warteschlange ist schon super nervig. Ich musste Ewigkeiten warten bis ein Tisch frei wurde. Ich glaube es war fast 1 Stunde. Dafür war aber das Essen lecker. Den Tee den wir hatten, wurde kontinuierlich aufgefüllt. Preislich wie üblich teuer.
